import numpy as np
#import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def forbedret_gram_schmidt(a):
  _, k = a.shape
  q = np.copy(a)
  r = np.zeros((k, k))
  for i in range(k):
    r[i, i] = np.linalg.norm(q[:, i])
    q[:, i] /= r[i,i]
    r[[i], i+1:] = q[:, [i]].T @ q[:, i+1:]
    q[:, i+1:] -= q[:, [i]] @ r[[i], i+1:]
  return q, r

  x = i % 20
  y = i //  20
  return (point2[0] - x - 0.05)**2 + (point2[1] - y - 0.5)**2 + (point2[2])**2
